02/03/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano kicked off his first official visit to Kosovo on Monday (1 March). He and Kosovo Prime Minister Bayram Rexhepi met at the Morina checkpoint on the Albania-Kosovo border to open a new customs terminal. Nano later met with UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri. Nano voiced Albania's support for the UN resolution on Kosovo and for talks between Serbian and Kosovo representatives. He also called for a broader Pristina-Brussels-Washington-Belgrade dialogue. Nano's schedule includes meetings with President Ibrahim Rugova and Parliamentary Speaker Nexhat Daci, as well as political leaders Hashim Thaci and Rramush Haradinaj. (ATA - 01/03/04)
